		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One trick (which was used in the NES port of Streemerz, IIRC) is to create the gameplay for 50Hz, and when running on an NTSC console simply skip 1 frame (i.e. don't run the game logic) every 5 frames. It worked pretty well apparently.</div><br /><br />It works &quot;okay&quot;, but it makes the game visibly jerky. I would have preferred if it ran smoothly, even if it meant a faster game.

		

